               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1450" notAfter="1499">
                     <p>The manuscript was written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace> in <origDate
                           notBefore="1450" notAfter="1499">the second half of the fifteenth
                           century</origDate>.</p>
                  </origin>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>According to the information on the AM-slips, <name type="person"
                           key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> got the leaves containing
                           <title>Adonias saga</title>, <title type="uniform">Hrólfs saga
                           Gautrekssonar</title>, <title type="uniform">Flóvents saga</title> and
                        some leaves of <title type="uniform">Hákonar saga Ívarssonar</title> from
                           <name type="person" key="BryTho001">Brynjólfur Þórðarson</name> in <date
                           when="1705">1705</date>. The remaining leaves containing <title
                           type="uniform">Hákonar saga Ívarssonar</title> and <title type="uniform"
                           >Sálus saga ok Nikanórs</title> he got from <name type="person"
                           key="GudSte001">Guðmundur Steinsson</name> in <date when="1721"
                           >1721</date>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
